Book of Hours, Use of Paris

Free Library of Philadelphia, Lewis E 93. Brittany?, France, Inclusion of Saints Yvo, Brioc and Corentine in the Litany (fol. 121r) may indicate that the manuscript was made for use in Brittany; first half of the 15th century. This Book of Hours of the Use of Paris was perhaps produced in Brittany, as the style of the fourteen large miniatures and contents of the calendar and litany suggest. The miniatures in the Hours of the Virgin for Sext, (Flight into Egypt, fol. 80v), None (Adoration of the Magi, fol. 85v), and Vespers (Presentation in the Temple, fol. 90v) diverge from the traditional iconographic sequence. Several of the foliate borders surrounding the miniatures contain Greek-inspired pseudo script.
